<subSubSection id="C309EEC62F6EFFE54EAFFE2DFD30FD96" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BACBD4D2F6EFFE54EAFFE2DFD30FD96" blockId="20.[151,1436,293,570]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54EAFFE2DFE28FE06" bold="true" box="[199,503,401,426]" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Distribution and habitat.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6EFFE54C69FE2DFD3AFE05" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[513,741,401,426]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54C69FE2DFD3AFE05" box="[513,741,401,426]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Loxopholis ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic to the archipelago of Anavilhanas, lower 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6EFFE54B3EFE2EFF08FE62" country="Uruguay" name="Rio Negro" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Negro River</collectingRegion>
, state of 
<collectingRegion id="49D773AF2F6EFFE54F54FE0AFE6AFE62" box="[316,437,438,462]" country="Brazil" name="Amazonas" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Amazonas</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F304FDDD2F6EFFE54FA8FE09FDDBFE62" box="[448,516,437,462]" name="Brazil" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="1328A1C82F6EFFE54C7CFE09FDB7FE62" box="[532,616,437,462]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1552,1574]" captionTargetBox="[157,1428,633,1523]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,625,1531]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 12. Distribution of examined material of Loxopholis ferreirai and Marinussaurus curupira." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/581987/files/figure.png" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
). It represents a rare case of endemicity of a terrestrial vertebrate species to an archipelago or island in 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6EFFE54F9BFE65FDB5FE5E" box="[499,618,473,498]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Meliolaceae" genus="Amazonia" kingdom="Fungi" order="Meliolales" pageId="20" pageNumber="195" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">Amazonia</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C13C6CE2F6EFFE54C1EFE65FC85FE5D" authority="Cope, 1868" authorityName="Cope" authorityYear="1868" box="[630,858,473,498]" class="Reptilia" family="Gymnophthalmidae" genus="Loxopholis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="20" pageNumber="171" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ferreirai">
<emphasis id="B967615F2F6EFFE54C1EFE65FC85FE5D" box="[630,858,473,498]" italics="true" pageId="20" pageNumber="171">Loxopholis ferreirai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is terrestrial and diurnal, inhabits the igapó forest present on the islands, where it is usually found in the leaf litter and under decomposing trunks and fallen palm leaves (personal communication with T. Ávila-Pires).
</paragraph>
